                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200112-46-victim490 t18200112-46-viclabel252"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18200112-46-crimeloc253">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200112-46-crimeloc253" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200112-46-crimeloc253" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200112-46-off250 t18200112-46-crimeloc253"></join>. On the 15th of December, about five o'clock in the evening, a person stepped into the shop, and took a hat off the rail - he kept his face towards the street. I pursued him up Featherstone-buildings, and lost him; I found the prisoner at Eagle-street watch-house with it. I believe him to be the man by his make, shape, and dress.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200112-46-person493">
